<HEADLINE> China to Provide Egypt with Grant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 19 (Xinhua) -- China will extend to Egypt a
non-refundable grant of 3.5 million U.S. dollars to set up a
hydroelectric power plant, said Egyptian Electricity Minister
Maher Abaza today.
</P>
<P>
Abaza made the remarks after his meeting with chairman of the
Egyptian Hydroelectric Power Projects Authority Moustafa
al-Guinidi. They discussed hydroelectric power projects that
Egypt will launch this year.
</P>
<P>
Construction work of the power plant in al-Fayoum Governorate,
about 120 kilometers south of Cairo, will start this year and the
plant is expected to start operation in 30 months.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian government will contribute 10 million Egyptian
pounds (3.4 million dollars) to the plant, Abaza said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
