<HEADLINE> China Builds Exhibition Hall For Late Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 19 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held in east
China's Jiangsu Province today to mark the beginning of work on an
exhibition hall for memorabilia of the late Premier Zhou Enlai.
</P>
<P>
Relatives of Zhou and people who worked with the late premier
attended the foundation-stone laying ceremony, along with more
than 1,000 provincial representatives, including provincial Party
secretary Chen Huanyu and provincial Governor Cheng Silin.
</P>
<P>
With the approval of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China, Huai'an, the hometown of the late premier, plans
to finish the construction program next March, to mark the 100th
anniversary of the statesman's birth.
</P>
<P>
Most of Zhou's personal items will be moved into the new
exhibition hall from Zhongnanhai, the central government and Party
headquarters, as soon as the hall is inaugurated.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition hall is expected to become an important place of
commemoration for Zhou, to keep revolutionary traditions alive
among local young people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
