<HEADLINE> Canadian Company Aids Chinese Students with Difficulties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Canada's Northern Telecom
in the past year promised a one-million-yuan donation to help
Chinese children from poor families go to school.
</P>
<P>
The funds have been spent on five primary schools in relatively
poor counties of Hebei Province, and will be used to support the
students in their study.
</P>
<P>
Northern Telecom is a new comer to China's national drive,
"Project Hope", where individuals, government offices, companies,
and organizations donate money and materials to help students in
poor areas finish their education.
</P>
<P>
Since the project was launched seven years ago, the China Youth
Development Foundation, organizer of the project, has received
about 800 million yuan (96 million US dollars) in donations from
at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Northern Telecom is the first foreign firm to co-operate with
this north China province. About a third of its telecommunications
equipment came from Northern Telecom.  
</P>
</TEXT>
