<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Commission to Host Rwandan Govt Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 19 (Xinhua) -- A Rwandan government
delegation will arrive here for a week-long visit from Monday at
the invitation of The Truth and Reconciliation Commission (TRC),
TRC Deputy Chairman Alex Boraine announced today.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Cape Town, Boraine said the
six-person Rwandan delegation, including government ministers and
senior advisers, would hold talks with government officials and
TRC commissioners during their stay in the country.
</P>
<P>
The visit is aimed at sounding out how South Africa can
achieve reconciliation between different races, observers here say.
</P>
<P>
All costs associated with this trip would be covered by the Belgian
government in terms of a funding agreement signed in November 1996
between the TRC and the Belgian government, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Referring to TRC's trip to Rwanda late last year, Boraine said,
"The purpose of our visit there was to provide technical assistance to
the Rwandan government in the formulation of their reparations policy
to assist victims of the Rwandan genocide in 1994."
</P>
<P>
After a week of meetings in Kigali, capital of Rwanda, it was felt
that both the Rwandans and the TRC would benefit from a broader range
of discussions on areas of mutual interest, added Boraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
