<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Conference on Publicity Work Held in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Heads of publicity departments
in China attended a national conference on publicity and
ideological work in Beijing from January 14 to 18, presided over
by Ding Guangen, head of the Propaganda Department of the CPC
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Their duty is to make the public aware of the two great events
this year: the return of Hong Kong and the convening of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC). Those
present said they agree that publicity and ideological work in
1997 should provide ideological backing for China's reforms,
development, and stability.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President and General Secretary of the CPC Central
Committee Jiang Zemin met with delegates and spoke of the
achievements of the country's publicity and ideological work in
the past year and what is needed next.
</P>
<P>
Participants concluded that overall China's publicity and
ideology work in 1996 was good, socialist ethical and cultural
progress being given full attention.
</P>
<P>
The conference took Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics and the Party's basic lines
and principles as its guide and urged all publicity workers to
concentrate on this year's two great events and to work hard to
arm the people with scientific theory, correctly guide public
opinion, provide people with lofty ideas, and encourage people
with outstanding works.
</P>
<P>
It also decided that publicity workers should grasp the overall
situation, work with one heart and one mind, and show a pioneering
spirit to be able to better serve the people and the socialist
system.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970120.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Protests to Russia Over Remarks on Sevastopol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine today protested to Russia
over Moscow Mayor Yuri Luzhkov's recent remarks insisting the
return of the disputed city of Sevastopol to Russia.
</P>
<P>
"Luzhkov...made unfriendly statements toward Ukraine, which
directly infringed on Ukraine's territorial integrity," a Foreign
Ministry statement said.
</P>
<P>
Describing Luzhkov's comments as "unacceptable," it said such
statements "negatively influence Ukrainian-Russian relations and
could bring about their deterioration."
</P>
<P>
During a surprise visit this weekend to Sevastopol, the home
port of the Black Sea Fleet on the Crimean peninsula, Luzhkov
said, "Sevastopol is a Russian glory city...we should defend the
right of Sevastopol to remain a Russian city."
</P>
<P>
Luzhkov's visit is likely to heighten tensions over the fate of
the fleet and the city, which have mired Russian-Ukrainian
relations since the disintegration of the Soviet Union in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Some 70 percent of Sevastopol's population are Russians, who
are also in the majority across Crimea. The Crimean peninsula
remained Russian territory until 1954, when former Soviet leader
Nikita Khrushchev turned it over to Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Luzhkov and his delegation were detained for much
of the night in the airport trying to leave Crimea at the end of
the surprise visit.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian police and customs officials accused Luzhkov's
bodyguard of illegally importing weapons as he was carrying a
gun. The bodyguard denied the accusation, saying he had declared
the gun upon arrival in the country.
</P>
<P>
Angered by the detention, Luzhkov called the act a "very
primitive, unintelligent and extremely insulting provocation."
</P>
<P>
"We have fallen victims to a very primitive, unintelligent and
extremely insulting provocation initiated by the leadership of
Kiev as a revenge for our open, clear and honest position," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970120.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Conference on Publicity Work Held in Beijing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference pointed out that publicity work this year must
center on economic construction and help promote the two
"fundamental shifts" in the economic system and mode of economic
growth, while taking opportunities to promote new developments and
conditions for socialist ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
The publicity and ideological offices must advocate the ideas
of "serving the people" and collectivism, promote a healthy
society, and use the opportunity of Hong Kong's return to educate
people about patriotism.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for the forthcoming 15th CPC National Congress,
efforts should be made to broaden education on the Party's basic
theories and lines to increase the public's faith in building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Several major tasks in publicity and ideological work for 1997
were listed, including upholding Deng Xiaoping's theories,
sticking to the central task of economic construction, increasing
promotion of ethical and cultural progress, correctly guiding
public opinion, and creating favorable social conditions for this
year's two great events.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen said that holding the banner of Deng Xiaoping's
theories high and sticking to the Party's basic lines are
fundamental to publicity work, which must be faithfully followed
for a long time.
</P>
<P>
"Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong thought, and Deng Xiaoping's
theories follow a continuous line of development and have formed a
unified scientific system. Deng Xiaoping's theories are Marxism
developed for contemporary China," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He explained that publicity workers must keep in line with the
Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core
ideologically, politically, and in their actions, and that
publicity work must serve the whole Party and the whole nation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
