<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970120.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Conference on Publicity Work Held in Beijing (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We must also cater to the needs of the masses and depend on
them, and do things that are welcomed by the masses, seriously and
satisfactorily," he said.
</P>
<P>
Publicity and ideology workers must try hard to popularize
scientific theories and promote lofty ideas, and seek healthy and
orderly development of publicity and culture, he pointed out,
adding that it is very important that consistency and stability be
maintained in publicity work, and that reality be examined deeply
in investigations and research for gathering experience.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that publicity and ideological work need a
team of dedicated and highly responsible officials, and that
"seriousness" in one's working attitude is the best criterion for
judging a person's dedication and sense of responsibility.
</P>
<P>
"Publicity and ideology workers should adopt an extremely
serious and responsible attitude toward the Party's and the
people's cause," he said, concluding by urging publicity and
ideology workers to do a solid job in welcoming the Party's 15th
national congress.
</P>
<P>
The conference was attended by publicity chiefs from all
provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions, a number of
central government departments, and the People's Liberation Army
and the Armed Police. 
</P>
