<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Launch Road Safety Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 19 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe police will launch
a countrywide road safety campaign to raise road users' awareness
on road accidents this year.
</P>
<P>
A police statement said today the campaign would be held in
the major cities and towns from January 27 to December 14 by the
police, the Zimbabwe Traffic Safety Board and the Automobile
Association of Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The topics, derived from main causes of road accidents,
include pedestrian behaviors, speed limits, driver condition,
motor vehicle defects, pedal cycle traffic, regulations on animal
drawn vehicles, drinking and driving and so on.
</P>
<P>
A series of lectures will be held with pamphlets to be issued
during the campaign. 
</P>
