<HEADLINE> US Balloonist Quits Round-the-World Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, CHICAGO, Jan 19 (AFP) - US balloonist Steve Fossett
decided to end his bid to circle to globe nonstop in India because
of a lack of fuel for his helium baloon, a spokesman for his
ground crew in Chicago said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Fossett, over Bhopal, India at 10:47 a.m. (1547 GMT), was to
seek to break the duration record -- for which he needed 15 more
hours aloft -- then land in India, Nick Saum, co-technical
director of the mission said.
</P>
<P>
"We think he's just going to park (hover) there, then land,"
Saum said, adding "we'll probably be at it again next year
because Steve has never given up before." 
</P>
</TEXT>
