<HEADLINE> Shanghai Beats Zhejiang in China First Division Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Oriental defeated the
Zhejiang Squirrels 68-53 in a Chinese men's basketball first
division match in Shanghai on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A Zhang Yong three-pointer and a free throw by Li De'en gave
Shanghai a 32-30 lead before the break but had to hammer down a
Zhejiang comeback in the second half.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's coach Li Qiuping said, "During most time of the game
the two teams were in a seesawing situation. Our offense was
reasonably good but we couldn't match them in rebounds."
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's coach Pan Jianping said his players suffered a lot
on poor shooting percentage from field.
</P>
<P>
In Dongguan, Guangdong Province, the Guangdong Tigers
squandered a 49-45 lead before losing to the visiting Shangdong
Flaming Bulls 89-94.
</P>
<P>
A successful "twin towers" strategy, implemented by Ji Shangmin
and Gong Xiaobin, worked well for the Flaming Bulls to stage the
second-half rally.
</P>
<P>
Also on Sunday, the Army Rockets maintained its lead in the
division after drubbing the Lianhang Eagles 105-64 in Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets collected 29 points from 14 wins and one loss, 1
point ahead of the runners-up Liaoning Hunters, who beat the
Beijing Ducks 95-85 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches, Jiangsu Nangang overwhelmed the Shenyang
Army Lions 85-73 and the Sichuan Pandas beat the Jinan Pegasus
83-73. 
</P>
</TEXT>
