<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Get Grain Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 19 (Xinhua) -- The Disaster Prevention
and Preparedness Commission of Ethiopia said today it has
distributed more than 11,000 tons of grain to the disaster
victims and the elders in the east in the past six months.
</P>
<P>
About 3,000 tons of wheat are being transported to aid
sufferers in Jijiga and Dire Dawa, said the commission, which
distributes food in a food-for-work way but the elders can get
food aid free.
</P>
<P>
The amount of food aid reached 253,118 tons for as many as 3.2
million people in Ethiopia in 1996, and the needed food aid will
drop to about 193,000 tons for a total of 1.93 million sufferers
this year. 
</P>
