<HEADLINE> Russia Supports Egypt's Mideast Policy: Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Russia fully supports Egypt's
policy on the Mideast peace process and the two countries share
identical views regarding a number of regional and international
issues, a Russian envoy said here today.
</P>
<P>
Boris Qozek, Russian President Boris Yeltsin's personal envoy,
hailed Egypt's "positive efforts and pioneer role" in the peace
process following his meeting with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Qozek, who arrived here Friday for a four-day visit, said he
discussed with Mubarak the latest developments of the Mideast
peace process and stressed on his country's full support for
Egypt's steps and stances toward the peace process, of which Russia
is a co-sponsor.
</P>
<P>
He said that they also discussed issues related to
bilateral relations and the programs that could enhance this
cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The Russian envoy said that he had brought with him a message
from Yeltsin to Mubarak, which touches upon the Russian-Egyptian
relations and the prospects of cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that further practical steps on this road
would be undertaken through Russia's participation in a number of
projects in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Qozek held talks with Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
on bilateral relations and cooperation in the political domain,
especially in pushing forward the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
They explored the potentials of establishing more joint
projects with a view to activating the economic cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Russian envoy also expressed his country's desire to raise
the level of trade exchange with Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
