<HEADLINE> King Hussein Reiterated Jordan's Support for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, January 19 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan  today
reiterated Jordan's continued support to the Palestinians for
their reinstatement of their rights on their national soil.
</P>
<P>
The king made the remarks in his telephone conversation with
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat, according to Radio Jordan.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein congratulated Arafat on the handover of the West
Bank town of Hebron to Palestinian rule.
</P>
<P>
Arafat today made his first official visit to Hebron to mark
the end of 30-year Israeli occupation of the West Bank city.
</P>
<P>
Arafat flew in a military helicopter to the tumultuous
welcome by tens of thousands of cheering Palestinians who
gathered near the former Israeli military headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, King Hussein today met with Mahmoud Abbas (Abu
Mazen), member of the Executive Committee of the Palestine
Liberation Organization, who is visiting Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Hussein told the Palestinian official that Jordan adheres to
its firm position in support of the Palestinians in all fields
until they regain their rights over their national territory.
</P>
<P>
He affirmed Jordan's support for the peaceful efforts as well
as the Middle East peace process until comprehensive, just and
lasting peace is achieved. 
</P>
