<HEADLINE> China And Vanuatu Sign Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng and visiting
Prime Minister Rialuth Serge Vohor of Vanuatu signed an agreement
at a ceremony in the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
The two governments also signed an exchange of notes on free
assistance granted by China to Vanuatu.
</P>
<P>
In the evening, the Chinese premier hosted a banquet in honor
of Vohor, who arrived here Sunday for an official visit at Li's
invitation.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the Vanuatu prime minister and his entourage
toured the Great Wall, and in the afternoon visited the Palace
Museum and Beijing's new railway station, one of the biggest in
Asia. 
</P>
