<HEADLINE> UN-Sponsored Forum on Aid for Afghan to Be Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 20 (Xinhua) -- A United Nations-sponsored
international meeting will be held from Tuesday to Wednesday in
Ashgabad, Turkmenistan to mobilize humanitarian aid for the
war-torn Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to rally international support for a
strategy that links urgently-required humanitarian assistance with
development and peace-making efforts, said the U.N. Office for
Coordination of Humanitarian Assistance to Afghanistan (UNOCHA) in
a news release issued here today.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 representatives from governments, the United
Nations system and non-governmental organizations will attend the
two-day event, said the news release.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is co-sponsored by the Department of Humanitarian
Affairs and the United Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
After 17 years of conflicts, Afghanistan is one of the poorest
countries in the world today.
</P>
<P>
The recent acceleration of the civil conflict has only
exacerbated the difficult living conditions of an already
impoverished population.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan conflict saw a sudden upsurge as the Taliban militia
launched a lightning strike last week against the Anti-Taliban
Alliance on the front north of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
The renewed fighting has brought an appeal for an immediate
ceasefire from U.N. special envoy to Afghanistan Norber Holl who
warned that the fighting would send false signals to the Ashgabad
forum.  
</P>
