<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Fall Amid Stronger Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stocks tumbled today with
the key Nikkei index losing more than 850 points at one time amid
the U.S. dollar's rise to a 46-month high against the Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The 225-issue Nikkei average closed at 17,480.34, down 609.70
points or 3.37 percent from Friday's close, dropping below 18,000
for the first time since January 10 on a closing basis.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all issues
on the First Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, fell 29.19
points or 2.10 percent to 1,359.17.
</P>
<P>
On the Tokyo Foreign Exchange, the dollar spurted to a 46-month
high of 117.90 yen at one point, reflecting an increasing appetite
for the U.S. currency backed by a strong economy in the United
States. 
</P>
