<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Official on Measures to Maintain HK's Status (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An said the Hong Kong SAR will keep its membership under the
name of "Chinese Hong Kong" in the world's largest multilateral
economic and trade organization, the World Trade Organization
(WTO), enjoying the rights and fulfilling the obligations of the
WTO independently.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining and strengthening the role Hong Kong is playing in
world trade and economy is in the best interests of both Hong Kong
and the mainland, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We set our primary objective of the economic and trade policy
towards Hong Kong as maintaining and strengthening Hong Kong's
status as a center of international trade, finance, shipping and
information," An said.
</P>
<P>
Guided by this, he said, "We will fully support a high degree
of freedom and openness in Hong Kong's status as an ideal arena
for concentration and flow of international capital.
</P>
<P>
"We'll actively support Hong Kong's effective market operating
mechanism and complete market legislation, encouraging Hong Kong
to bring its market mechanism into full play and maintaining its
environment for open and fair competition.
</P>
<P>
"We stand ready to support Hong Kong in its efforts to expand
foreign economic and trade relations, and further enhance its
reputation as an international metropolitan city provided the
state's sovereignty and interests are not undermined."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, extra efforts shall be taken to strengthen
economic cooperation between the mainland and Hong Kong and make
better use of the advantages the two areas enjoy, and thus create
favorable conditions for mutual prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The implementation of these laws and regulations after July 1
this year and a close economic and trade cooperation between the
two areas will further strengthen and advance Hong Kong's status
as a center of international trade, finance, shipping and
information, he pointed out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
