<HEADLINE> Denmark, Mexico Beat Peru, United States in U.S. Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Denmark beat Peru 2-1 and
Mexico won over the United States 2-0 today in the U.S. Cup
soccer tournament in Pasadena, California.
</P>
<P>
In the first match, Denmark's Soren Andersen made the first
goal at the 8th minute. The winner was netted in the 81st minute
through a 20 meter drive.
</P>
