goal at the 3rd minute while captain Alberto Garcia Aspe added the
second goal at the 68th minute.
</P>
<P>
It was the first victory for the Mexican team to win over the
Americans in the last six attempts, including a stunning loss to
the United States in the 1995 Copa America.
</P>
<P>
It was Mexico's first victory against the U.S. team on U.S.
soil since a 1-0 win in Dallas in 1974.
</P>
<P>
For the Americans, it was the second loss in the four-nation
tournament. On Friday, Peru beat the United States 1-0.
</P>
<P>
The tournament match was a warm-up for crucial group play in
which the United States, Mexico, Canada, Jamaica, El Salvador and
Costa Rica will be vying for three spots in the 1998 World Cup
finals in France. 
