<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Official on Measures to Maintain HK's Status (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- China will fully ensure Hong
Kong's autonomous participation in multilateral and bilateral
economic and trade activities according to the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
An Min, assistant minister for Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, made the position clear when answering a journalist's
question on what measures China is going to take to boost Hong
Kong's status as a center for finance, trade, shipping and
telecommunications after it returns to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He said that based on the principle of "one country, two
systems," Hong Kong's capitalist society, economic system, and way
of life will remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
On the economic and trade front, Hong Kong will keep the
current economic and trade system, retaining its standing as a
free port.
</P>
<P>
He said Hong Kong will continue to pursue a free trade policy,
enabling the free flow of commodities, invisible assets and
capital. Additionally, Hong Kong will enjoy a high degree of
autonomy in administrative legislation and management, enacting
and implementing economic and trade laws, policies and measures on
their own.
</P>
<P>
"China will fully ensure Hong Kong's autonomous participation
in multilateral and bilateral economic and trade activities,
provided the Basic Law is not violated," he said.
</P>
<P>
In keeping with the stipulations of the Basic Law or with the
authorization of the central government, he said, the Hong Kong
SAR, a separate customs territory, can keep and advance its
economic and trade relations with various countries and regions,
under the name "Chinese Hong Kong."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
