<HEADLINE> All Sugar Produced in Uganda to Comprise Vitamin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is planning to install
and open factories producing sugar comprising vitamin A by
December this year, reported the local daily The New Vision
today.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan Steering Committee on Sugar Fortification has
approved a plan which requires all sugar the country produces
should comprise Vitamin A nutrient in a meeting held resently in
Lugazi, 50 kilometers east of Kampala.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, technical experts will check the quality and
draft standards for sugar production.
</P>
<P>
The plan also calls for a survey on sugar consumption patterns
in the four regions of the country.
</P>
<P>
Uganda, with a population of 19 million, consumes more than
180,000 tons of sugar a year. 
</P>
