<HEADLINE> Anhui Province Seeks Closer Ties with Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Eastern Chinese Province
of Anhui is a reliable partner in economic cooperation for Hong
Kong, Macao and Southeast Asian countries and it now seeks an even
closer tie with Hong Kong, an official of the provincial
government said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of an investment-oriented
campaign here today, Deputy Governor Zhang Runxia said that Anhui
achieved the fastest economic development among Chinese provinces
during the Eighth Five-Year Plan period which ended in 1995, with
an average annual increase of 14.1 percent in the gross domestic
product.
</P>
<P>
Anhui's total import and export value for the period was 7.4
billion U.S. dollars, with an average annual increase of 25
percent, she said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's total investment in Anhui during the period was 1.3
billion U.S. dollars, about 43 percent of the total value of
overseas investment in the province. Anhui's total value of
imports and exports in 1996, which is the first year of the Ninth
Five-Year Plan period, was 2.75 billion U.S. dollars and that for
the trade with Hong Kong was 410 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that economic cooperation between Anhui and Hong
Kong will enter a new stage on the basis of mutual benefit and
prosperity," she added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
