<HEADLINE> PA Official: Negotiations Beyond Hebron to Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Higher Education Minister of the
Palestinian Authority (PA) Hanan Ashrawi today said negotiations
with Israel on pending issues in the transitional phase after the
Hebron redeployment will start soon.
</P>
<P>
Negotiators from the two sides would discuss a number of
issues, including the opening of safe passages between the West
Bank and the Gaza Strip, the Gaza Airport and the release of
Palestinian prisoners, the minister said in an interview this
morning with Voice of Arab radio.
</P>
<P>
Some issues in the transitional phase require an executive
protocol such as the security passages between the West Bank and
Gaza, while others do not need talks, namely, the release of
Palestinian detainees and prisoners of war in Israeli jails, she
added.
</P>
<P>
Ashrawi termed Hebron accord as a mere executive protocol that
has political dimensions because it is the first accord the
present Israeli government signed with the PA.
</P>
<P>
Israel completed troop pullbacks from 80 percent of Hebron last
Friday under a deal initialed Wednesday between the Palestinians
and Israelis after months of tortuous negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Under the Note for the Record provided by the the U.S. as an
annex to the Hebron agreement, the two sides will resume the
above-mentioned talks immediately after the redeployment.
</P>
<P>
Within two months, they will begin talks on a final peace
agreement, which will decide their final borders, the future of
Jerusalem and the 144 Jewish settlements in the West Bank and Gaza
Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
