<HEADLINE> Nigeria Rebukes West on Human Rights Accusation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government has
criticised the western countries for false accusation of its human
rights violations, the official "New Nigeria" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Paul Nwokedi, Chairman of the Nigerian Human Rights
Commission, was quoted by the paper as saying that he is
disgusted about the double standard set by western countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the protection of fundamental rights is enshrined in
the Nigerian constitution and has been respected, as Nigeria is a
party to 13 major international human rights conventions.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that the Nigerian government has recently set up a
committee which reviews cases of detained persons every two
months, and has released more than 20 persons since its
inauguration.
</P>
<P>
The chairman explained that the commission has the mandate to
monitor and investigate all alleged cases of human rights
violation, to assist victims to seek redress and remedies, to
engage in human rights studies and assist the government on the
formation of human rights policy. 
</P>
