<HEADLINE> HK Manufacturers' Orders-on-Hand Decreases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong
manufacturers' orders-on-hand for local production in November
1996 decreased by five percent over the same month of 1995,
according to official statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
The value of orders of the fabricated metal products industry
increased by nine percent in November 1996, compared with the same
period in 1995. The textiles industry and the wearing apparel
industry both recorded a slight increase of one percent, compared
with the consecutive declines for a number of months.
</P>
<P>
However, the value of orders in the printing and publishing
industry decreased 16 percent, while the plastic products industry
and the electronic products industry both recorded a decrease of
11 percent. 
