<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Suffers From African Sanctions Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's cement export has lost
1.6 billion Kwacha (about 1.2 million U.S. Dollars) since last
July due to the sanctions imposed on Burundi by some African
countries.
</P>
<P>
The loss was accrued by Chilaga Cement Plc's export to
Burundi. Chilaga Cement Plc is the sole cement producer in
Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Zambia stopped its cement export to Burundi last July when it
joined other African countries in imposing sanctions on Burundi
to protest against the military coup staged by present President
Pierre Buyoya.
</P>
<P>
The sanctions also affected Mpulungu Port and surface
transporters who lost 80 million Kwacha (about 62,000 U.S.
Dollars) and 800 million Kwacha (about 620,000 U.S. Dollars)
respectively in service charges.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Foreign Minister Lawrence Shimba reaffirmed recently
that his country will maintain sanctions on Burundi, alleging
that Buyoya's has continued to kill members of opposition
parties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
