<HEADLINE> Japanese Airliner Reported Hijacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 20 (Xinhua) - A Japanese passenger plane was
hijacked today on a domestic flight from Osaka to Fukuoka in
southern Japan, NHK television said.
</P>
<P>
The hijacker, a man who appeared to be about 40 years old, took
the All Nippon Airways Boeing 777 hostage shortly after the
aircraft landed at Fukuoka airport with 192 people on board.
</P>
<P>
However, he was arrested by police 45 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Nobody was injured in the incident, during which passengers
were reportedly unaware of what was going on until being led off
from the aircraft. 
