<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents in Vietnam Kill 6,000 in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents killed 16
persons and wounded 59 others in Vietnam on an average day in
1996, the Interior Ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
The accidents, totaling 20,000 last year, claimed the lives of
6,000 people and injured 21,700 others, making it the single
greatest cause for the loss of life in many years.
</P>
<P>
The number of traffic accidents and subsequent deaths and
injuries increased by 22 percent, 3.8 percent and 26.5 percent
respectively compared with 1995, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
In spite of great efforts made to implement decrees on traffic
safety, violation of traffic law and regulations and illegal
occupation of roads and street pavement remain a big problem.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the police throughout the country handled more than
1.8 million cases of traffic law and regulation breaches, and
revoked the licenses of 2,645 motor vehicle drivers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of newly-licensed cars and motorcycles
increased by 17 percent in Vietnam but roads were still narrow and
degrading in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
