<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Enhances Financial Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The government of southwest
China's Sichuan province and local banks have made efforts to
improve financial control to ensure smooth implementation of the
state's moderately-tight financial policy and improve finance
operations.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the Sichuan People's Bank checked all the subordinate
banks in the province and discovered 1.03 billion yuan (12.4
million US dollars) worth of improper business practices and 73.05
million US dollars worth of improper foreign exchange trade.
</P>
<P>
In checking accounts, around 33 organizations were cited for
illegal operations, and paid 783,000 yuan in fines, and 583
financial organizations were discovered with 685 illegal
contracts, involving 24.59 million yuan. Thorough checks on
foreign currency exchange business revealed more than a billion US
dollars in illegal deals.
</P>
<P>
The financial control resulted in a record amount of deposits
of 314.05 billion yuan and loans of 335.95 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
