<HEADLINE> Southwest China Railway Bureau To Add Trains For Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Preparation in China's
southwest for the lunar new year festival (on February 7) are
being made, according to an official with the Chengdu Railway
Bureau, who says that Yunnan, Guizhou, and Sichuan will add 34
temporary passenger trains to improve transportation for transient
workers.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that, during the 50-day Spring Festival peak
period from January 8 to March 8, southwestern railways will
handle 11 million passagers, up 160,000 from the same period last
year. The greatest number of passengers will be transient rural
workers.
</P>
<P>
Railway stations in Chengdu, Chongqing, Guiyang, and Kunming
will sell return tickets to students, and more ticket-booking
offices will be opened at stations helping large numbers of
passengers. Ticket office hours will also be extended and special
waiting areas for transient workers and students will be arranged.
</P>
