<HEADLINE> Improved Mainland-HK Economic Ties to Boost Businessmen's Confidence In Future (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- An Min, assistant minister for
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, said today he believes
that people with vision will remain confident in the future of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
An made these remarks here when answering journalists'
questions on whether the improvement of economic ties and trade
between the Chinese mainland and Hong Kong will deepen the faith
of the Hong Kong business community.
</P>
<P>
Noting the close and good economic relations and trade that
exist between the mainland and Hong Kong, An said both the
mainland and Hong Kong have complemented each other and worked
together for common development, particularly since the former
initiated the policy of reform and opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Their economic ties and trade are "forging ahead with a sound
momentum of rapid, comprehensive and in-depth development," he
said.
</P>
<P>
An said that the smooth transfer and long-term prosperity and
stability of Hong Kong are in keeping with the trend of the times
and the aspirations of the people. And the Chinese government
will, in strict compliance with the Basic Law, implement the
policies of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong," a high-degree
of autonomy and "one country, two systems" after july 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
He said the advantages enjoyed by the mainland and Hong Kong
will be brought into full play, and Hong Kong's status as an
international economic and trade center will be further
strengthened.
</P>
</TEXT>
