were set up, representing an increase of 12 percent over one year
ago.
</P>
<P>
A recent questionnaire distributed by the British Chamber of
Commerce in Hong Kong shows that 98 percent of British business
people in Hong Kong will stay on in Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
The assistant minister said the survey also indicates that
U.S. business people are largely confident in their investment in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
To date, he said, 180 large U.S. corporations have moved their
headquarters for the Asia-Pacific region to Hong Kong.
