<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Acid Tolerant Bean on Experiment in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- A productive seed variety of
the acid tolerant bean has been found in Africa and scientists
said it will be introduced on Uganda's soil.
</P>
<P>
local press reports quoted Charles Wortmann, a scientist of
Kampala's Kawanda Research Institute, as saying that the variety,
suitable to most soil of east and central Africa, had been
defined after a six-year extensive screening starting from 1990.
</P>
<P>
The seeds of the variety were acquired in Malawi and spread to
Rwanda as Lunze lubanga, a soil scientist responsible for the
job, gave some seeds to his wife for experiment in her garden,
which was proved very successful and welcomed by local farmers
who named it as "Mwa Sole".
</P>
<P>
The merit of acid tolerant "Mwa Sole" seeds is its bigger size
despite earlier definition that acid tolerant beans are
small-seed ones.
</P>
<P>
Acid soil is the main constraint to land productivity in most
parts of central and east africa. And researchers in different
countries including Uganda are at present doing more experiment
on the seeds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
