<HEADLINE> 32 Killed As Bus Falls into River in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 32 people were
killed and 12 injured when a private mini-bus carrying a wedding
party fell into a river in northern India's Punjab state on
Sunday, the Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
Local police sources said 32 bodies were recovered while divers
were looking for more bodies in the Kali Beini river.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the ill-fated mini-bus lost control of the
vehicle while negotiating a curve over the bridge on the river.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations were hampered for a while by continuous rains
since the morning, the report said.  
</P>
