<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 08:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran to Award Oil Contracts to Foreign Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Iran is to award foreign
companies two multi-million-dollar oil field contracts that could
provoke U.S. sanctions, state-owned English daily Tehran Times
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper said the National Iranian Oil Company (NIOC) will
award contracts to develop its Soroush and Balal offshore oil
fields by the end of March.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a NIOC official as saying "final proposals
of the interested companies have been received by the NIOC and the
winners will be announced by the end of March.
</P>
<P>
Seyed Jalilian, NIOC's director of offshore division, said
that European, Asian and Iranian companies are being considered
for the work at the two fields.
</P>
<P>
However, the official did not specify how many foreign
companies are taking part in the bidding to carry out
the development work at the offshore fields.
</P>
<P>
Last August, U.S. President Bill Clinton signed a bill to
punish foreign companies which invest 40 million dollars or more
a year in Iran, which was accused by the U.S. of sponsoring
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Analysts estimate that contracts to develop Soroush and Balal
could total some 250 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies would get a return for their investment
under the NIOC's so-called buy-back formula which gives payment in
the form of oil and gas produced at the field.
</P>
<P>
Soroush, which was heavily damaged during the 1980-88
Iraq-Iran war, and the untapped Balal fields are set to
produce some 130,000 barrels of oil a day at the end of the
decade.
</P>
<P>
To thwart U.S. sanctions, the Iranian oil industry has
announced a total of 11 oil and gas projects worth at least 7
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Iran said that more than 120 foreign oil and gas companies
offered their bids for the Iranian oil and gas sectors.
</P>
<P>
Iran, with 92 billion barrels of crude oil reserves, is the
second largest oil exporter in the world. It pumps 3.6 million
barrels of oil and exports 2.5 million barrels of crude oil every
day.
</P>
<P>
The oil industry is the pillar of Iran's economy. Iran earns
about 16 billion to 18 billion dollars by exporting crude oil a
year, and the oil export revenue accounts for about 70 percent of
the total export of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
