<DOCNO> XIE19970120.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu Scientists Perform Miracles in Desert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- They are known as the
magnificent seven -- young Chinese scientists who have performed
what experts described as nothing short of a miracle.
</P>
<P>
The seven from Gansu Province, northwest China, headed to the
inhospitable Gobi Desert in Tibet where the sand rules supreme.
</P>
<P>
But using scientific skills, the young scientists have
harvested crops, fruits and successfully introduced some 100 kinds
of flowers to create a thriving garden 3,890 meters above sea
level in desert on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Desert experts in Lanzhou, capital of Gansu Province, believe
that the young people from Lanzhou Institute of Desert Research of
the Chinese Academy of Sciences have created miracles by
establishing the world highest altitude desert demonstration zone.
</P>
<P>
The scientists have successfully grown maize, wheat, fruits,
melons and flowers directly in the Gobi desert and on an
artificial pasture in a 113-hectare desert demonstration zone.
</P>
<P>
Starting in 1994, they have changed a desolate and uninhabited
area in Xigaze in the Tibet Autonomous Region, building canals,
levelling land, planting shelter forest, improving natural
grassland and developing ecological experimental areas.
</P>
<P>
Tibet has 210,000 hectares of land that has turned into desert
and is threatened by shifting sand and desertification, hindering
local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
After years' efforts, the seven young scientists have sought
the best time and best method for plant growing in the plateau's
Gobi desert.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in Tibet's history that trees have been
successfully planted in the rainy season. The survival rate of the
trees has reached 99 percent whereas the survival rate of trees
planted in the autumn months has reached 95 percent.
</P>
<P>
They also made a breakthrough in introducing water melons,
strawberries, melons and grapes, reaping a good harvest in the
same year of the planting. The fruits are big in size, sweet
tasting and high in water content.
</P>
<P>
The scientists also obtained a high wheat yield by applying
advanced technology in plastic sheet-covered wheat growing. The
wheat output reached 6,825 kg per hectare, 27.3 percent higher
with conventional methods.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the demonstration zone has aroused the
interest of many Tibetans living nearby. They volunteered to
participate in work in the zone to learn about the new technology.
</P>
<P>
The local government has decided to spread the technology to
other parts of the Gobi desert area starting from this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
