<HEADLINE> South China Region To Make Better Use Of Overseas Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in southwest China has said it will use more overseas
capital from large enterprises and financial groups for
infrastructure contruction and upgrading agricultural and
industrial technology.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Fulin, Secretary of the regional committee of the
Communist Party of China, says the region is encouraging overseas
investment for tapping oceanic resources, developing hi-tech
industry and tourism, and building housing.
</P>
<P>
Overseas funding is welcome as direct investment in
transforming large state enterprises technically and for producing
market-oriented products.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years the region has had imports and exports
worth 10 billion US dollars and has used just over 3 billion US
dollars worth of overseas capital. It had 6,301 registered
overseas-funded enterprises by the end of 1995. 
</P>
