<HEADLINE> Chinese, Congolese Defense Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian told his Congolese counterpart Francois Ayayen that he
believes Ayayen's current visit to China is bound to promote the
further development of friendship and cooperation between the two
countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of the Central Military
Commission and state councillor, made the remark here this morning
during his talks with Ayayen, who is the first Congolese defense
minister to come to China since the two countries set up
diplomatic ties 30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Ayayen's China visit, Chi said that
China and Congo are friendly countries enjoying traditional
friendship, adding that bilateral relations and cooperation in
various fields have been growing smoothly.
</P>
<P>
There has been further development in cooperation in political,
economic and cultural spheres in recent years, Chi said, adding
that the Chinese government and people value such a friendship
between China and Congo, and are willing to further promote
friendly cooperative relations on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit.
</P>
<P>
Ayayen said Congo and China have long-term, friendly and
cooperative ties which have stood the test of time, expressing the
hope that his current visit will further develop the relations
between the two nations and their militaries.
</P>
<P>
The Congolese government upholds the "One China" stance and
supports China's great cause of peaceful reunification, added
Ayayen.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the guests on China's economic development and
the modern construction of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Ayayen arrived here as guest of Chi, who presided over a
welcome ceremony prior to the meeting, and accompanied him in a
honor guard review.  
