<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Makes Progress in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The foreign trade volume of
east China's Zhejiang Province soared 16.1 percent to hit 13.38
billion US dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Of the total volume, export was valued at 9.33 billion US
dollars, 10.5 percent up from the previous year's figure, while
the import totalled 4.05 billion US dollars, a 31.5 percent rise.
</P>
<P>
Export of overseas-funded or export-oriented firms made up 70
percent the province's total.
</P>
<P>
The province approved 1,208 overseas-funded enterprises last
year. Though the number of firms went down by 33.8 percent, the
volume of overseas funds absorbed increased by 20.9 percent at 1.5
billion US dollars, an all time high, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
Information about one-tenth of the newly-approved projects was
available on the Internet, which has made them more competitive in
international bidding.
</P>
<P>
Investment in 146 of the projects exceeded 10 million US
dollars for each.
</P>
<P>
The structure of overseas investment became more rational last
year. Investment in infrastructure and basic industries involved
a combined contractual value of 330 million US dollars, accounting
for 11 percent of Zhejiang's total contractual value, and setting
a record high.  
</P>
</TEXT>
