<HEADLINE> World Bank To Help Africa in Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank is planning to
assist African countries in campaign to achieve environmentally
sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
A bank report reaching here today said the world's largest
financial organization wili work with local communities and
governments to achieve this goal.
</P>
<P>
Major targets of the plan include achieving food security,
stabilizing population growth, influencing migration toward a
better distribution of the population, making urbanization
sustainable and managing energy, water and other natural
resources in an integrated and sustainable fashion.
</P>
<P>
