<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flowers Bring Sweet Scented Riches to Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Flowers have provided the sweet
scent of success in Shandong Province, a major grain producer in
east China.
</P>
<P>
Flower growing has blossomed so much in recent years that it
has now become one of the five key agricultural industries in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Xin Yunyan, head of the Shandong Flower Association, told
Xinhua that his province has grown nearly 10,000 hectares of
flowers with the gross output reaching 47.5 million U.S. dollars
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
He added that the flower growing acreage will be increased to
13,000 hectares, with an annual output value of 187 million
dollars by 2000.
</P>
<P>
He said the booming of the industry is attributed to the
improvement in people's living and cultural standards.
</P>
<P>
The Shandong provincial government believed that flower growing
had a great potential, and listed it as one of the five key
industries in its agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
So far, the province has built five flower growing bases
according to plan. They include the Heze peony and Chinese
herbaceous peony base, Weifang azalea base, Pingyin rose base,
Laizhou Chinese rose base, and Pingyi honeysuckles base.
</P>
<P>
Heze has become China's biggest peony production and sales
center with 133 hectares of peony growing area.
</P>
<P>
The province has also developed more than 20 items of new
technology in flower growing and flower land management, and
applied research findings in its flower bases.
</P>
<P>
With traditional peony growing methods, the flower usually
blossoms from mid-April, but by using the flower-accelerating
technology, it can blossom during the Spring Festival, the most
important holiday in China which usually falls in February.
</P>
<P>
A number of farmers have become rich by growing flowers. Li
Hongru, a flower grower in Huanglou town, Qingzhou city, started
growing flowers in 1981, and now has become manager of the
privately-run Shandong Wanhong Flower Company with 320 employees.
</P>
<P>
His company has grown 21 hectares of flowers of various kinds
and built up a flower trade hall of 16,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, his company realized 500,000 U.S. dollars worth of
profits and taxes.
</P>
<P>
His son and daughter, who were employees of state-own
enterprises, gave up their jobs and help him run the company.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
