<HEADLINE> Tanzania Scoops 300 Million Dollars From Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania earned 322.38
million U.S. Dollars last year from 326,194 foreign tourists,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Principal Tourist Information Officer of the Tanzania Tourist
Board (TTB), Jnhnson Manase, told reporters Sunday that this
registered an increase of 32,360 tourists as compared to the
previous year when 293,834 visited the country and brought in
258.14 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
"We have improved the promotion effort by increasing our
participation in international tourism fairs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Manase said that previously Tanzania had no publicity office
abroad and that is why the number of visitors who came into the
country was very little compared to the number of attractions
found in the country.
</P>
<P>
By the year 2000, Tanzania is expected to receive 495,950
tourists and earn about 799.64 million Dollars, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Manase urged the government to increase fund
allocations to TTB to enable it fulfil its plans which include
advertising Tanzania abroad.  
