<HEADLINE> Balloonist to End Global Nonstop Flight in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- American balloonist Steve
Fossett told air traffic controllers Monday he would quit his
attempt to circle the world and soon land in eastern India because
of a fuel shortage.
</P>
<P>
His ground crew in Chicago said Fossett had tied a listing
record of been six-day, 16 minute in the balloon at about 11:30
a.m., (0600 GMT) but he had to be in the air for another hour for
a new record to be recognized.
</P>
<P>
At the time he matched the old record, he was said to be flying
at an altitude of just under 350 meters and a speed of less than
16 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The balloon is 780 kilometers southeast of New Delhi and
expected to land Monday near the village of Babatpur, 11
kilometers south of an airport. 
