<HEADLINE> Van Roost Marks Her Second Upset at Australian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Dominique van Roost
of Belgium marked her second upset at the Australian Open on
Monday, ousting 15th seeded American Chanda Rubin in straight sets
to enter her first ever quarter-final in a grand slam event.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost, who upset world number two Arantxa Sanchez Vicario
in the third round on Saturday, overcame a sore elbow and strokes
her win over Rubin 7-5, 6-4 in one hour and 28 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Van Roost, world ranked 43, will play either American 14th seed
Mary Joe Fernandez or Patty Schnyder of Switzerland in the quarter
finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
