<HEADLINE> Bank of China Opens Network in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Automated Teller Machines
(ATMs) in Hangzhou, the capital of east China's Zhejiang Province,
are now accepting the Bank of China's cards, according to Wang
Bingnan, president of the Hangzhou branch of the Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 Hangzhou residents have Great Wall cards, with
which they can get money from ATM machines in 28 of China's cities.
</P>
<P>
The network is the result of joint efforts between Hangzhou's
information department and credit card departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
