<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Improve Industrial Boilers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The UN Global environment
Facility (GEF) will set aside 30 million US dollars for setting up
an efficient industrial boiler project in China.
</P>
<P>
An official with the country's industrial boiler association
has disclosed that the nine-item project's goal is to improve the
environment by introducing advanced technology, improving thermal
efficiency of boilers, and reducing environmental pollution.
</P>
<P>
It is predicted that the need for industrial boilers will
increase by three to eight percent annually to keep up with rapid
development. But, traditional coal boilers cause severe pollution
and they need to be replaced. In some cities in China, gas boilers
have taken the place of coal ones.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank will get some foreign boiler manufactures to
come to China to cooperate with China's boiler industry.
</P>
<P>
The Third International Exhibition of Boilers, Subsidiary
Engines and Equipment is scheduled for Shanghai in November.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
