<HEADLINE> Largest Exhibition Center Under Construction in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Central China's largest
international exhibition and convention center recently went under
construction in Wuhan, the provincial capital of Hubei.
</P>
<P>
The 500-million-yuan project is a multi-function complex
featuring space for trade, tourism, exhibition and recreational
activities.
</P>
<P>
Funded by the Huayun Real Estate Development Company in Wuhan,
the property, which covers 130,000 square meters of total floor
space, contains one 18-story building and one 21-story building.
</P>
<P>
The 18-story facility includes hotel rooms, a shopping center,
a beauty parlor, a fitness center, and bank outlets, with two
tennis courts, a golf court and a rooftop swimming pool.
</P>
<P>
The 21-story building will be used as an exhibition and
convention center, and will have two helicopter landing pads on
the roof.
</P>
<P>
Property market analysts believe that when it is put into use,
the center will serve as an important showpiece of the regional
opening-up to the outside world, and will play a major role in
promoting the regional economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
