<DOCNO> XIE19970120.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Produce 230,000 Santana Cars This year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will produce 230,000
Santana cars in 1997, and expects to chalk up 35 billion yuan in
sales volume.
</P>
<P>
The city made 200,000 Santana cars last year and sold 196,000,
with the market share of Santana cars standing at 52 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai started its car-manufacturing industry in 1956 and had
altogether produced 47,000 Shanghai-brand cars by 1985, when
Shanghai Volkswagen Corporation, a Sino-German joint venture, was
established and became operational.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the joint venture had produced 746,000
Santana cars, including 104,000 Santana-2000 type luxury cars made
last year.
</P>
<P>
The corporation has continued to adjust its product mix
according to market demands and has worked to improve product
quality, reduce production cost, and perfect marketing and
after-sale service networks -- all designed to help the company
maintain an edge in China's fiercely competitive car market.
</P>
<P>
According to a company executive, the localization ratio of
common type Santana cars is 90 percent, and 80 percent for the
Santana-2000 luxury type cars. The joint venture now has 113
dealerships and has established 332 repair centers across the
country.
</P>
<P>
To expand its market, the company has invested heavily in
building a modern storage and transport system. In addition to the
existing eight freight trains, four ships for shipping service on
the Yangtze River and three ocean-going vessels, the company will
soon purchase two more freight trains and import another sea
vessel to increase its annual storage and transport capacity to
300,000 cars.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's car-manufacturing industry has helped the
development of related sectors in other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The company now has 150 members for the localization of the
Santana cars and 230 factories from across the country have
provided it with spare parts needed in the production of Santana
cars. The annual output value of such auxiliary services is 15
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
All spare parts suppliers are expected to pass the ISO9002
international quality guarantee certification test this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
