<HEADLINE> Gore Expected to Visit Japan in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Vice President Al Gore is
expected to visit Japan for talks with government leaders prior to
his trip to Beijing, China, scheduled for late March, according to
the report of a leading Japanese daily.
</P>
<P>
Quoting sources from Beijing, the Yomiuri Shimbun report said
Sunday that U.S. officials have been discussing the proposed visit
to Tokyo with the Japanese government.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Gore wishes to discuss U.S. policy
regarding China with Tokyo, as Washington and Beijing are set to
improve their bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
An exchange of visits by U.S. President Bill Clinton and his
Chinese counterpart, Jiang Zemin, was announced last year.
</P>
<P>
The report said Gore's talks with Japanese leaders are likely
to reaffirm the Japan-U.S. security relationship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
