<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets Hands Bulls Its Fifth Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Hakeem Olajuwon scored 30
points Sunday to lead the Houston Rocket to a 102-86 home victory
over the Chicago Bulls, the only fifth defeat of the Bulls this
season.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian-born National Basketball Association star center
also pulled down 16 rebounds sparked 19 consecutive Houston points
in the final five minutes.
</P>
<P>
Neither club was at full strength. Houston's Charles Barkley
was sidelined by a sprained ankle and Chicago's Dennis Rodman was
sitting the second game of an 11-game suspension for kicking a
photographer.
</P>
<P>
Clyde Drexler contributed 17 points, 10 rebounds and 11 assists
for the Rockets while forward Kevin Willis ignored a back injury
to added 20 points.
</P>
<P>
Michael Jordan scored 26 points to pace the Bulls (34-5), who
need two victories to reach the half-season mark on a pace to
match their unprecedented 72-10 record of last season.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets (31-9) own the league's second-best record. They
avenged a 110-86 defeat at Chicago last weekend that came when
they were at the end of a long road trip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
