<HEADLINE> Malaysia Welcomes Israeli Military Pullout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
from Hebron
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has welcomed the
Israeli military withdrawal from the West bank city of Hebron,
hoping that it will pave the way for a comprehensive solution to
the problems in West Asia.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia would continue to monitor the situation in West Asia
with keen interest, Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said.
</P>
<P>
"We wish to see follow-up action taken by Israel in the
on-going peace process," he was quoted by the Malaysian national
news agency Bernama as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said it was Malaysia's hope that Israel would
continue to move forward to ensure the success of the peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians have taken control of most of Hebron after
protracted negotiations between their President Yasser Arafat and
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.  
