<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Explains Sino-African Friendship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, January 19 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-African friendship was
well established and is smoothly developing, said Chinese
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen, commenting on his
last week's visit to five African countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who arrived here on Saturday for an official goodwill
visit to Portugal, paid official visits to the African nations of
Niger, Equatorial Guinea, Sao Tome and Principe, Mauritania and
Cape Verde last week.
</P>
<P>
Qian told reporters of Xinhua News Agency and the Central
Television Station (CCTV) that what impressed him the most during
his tour of Africa was that these countries are enjoying stable
domestic situation and prosperous economic development after five
to six years of turbulence caused by the change of the
international situation.
</P>
<P>
Now, African countries are continuing their efforts to seek
their own political system and developing road according to their
own specific situation, Qian added.
</P>
<P>
African countries expressed their appreciation of China's
attention to them and welcomed China's position that all nations,
no matter big or small, rich or poor, are equal, he said.
</P>
<P>
African nations are expecting more effective assistance from
the international community, rather than intervention in their own
internal affairs, he added.
</P>
<P>
Asked about China's principle position about the election of
the secretary-general of the United Nations, Qian said that the
result was fair.
</P>
<P>
A secretary-general from Africa, a continent of more than 50
countries, should enjoy the same right as those from other regions
to serve two terms, said Qian.
</P>
<P>
The election of Kofi Annan as the U.N. secretary-general showed
that the international community has confidence in and
expectations of Africa, he said.
</P>
<P>
As for the resumption of the diplomatic relations between China
and Niger and Taiwan's diplomatic efforts in this region, Qian
said that he is satisfied about the smooth development of the
Sino-Niger relations on a new basis and is optimistic about the
future of the relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the past few years, the Taiwan authorities took
the advantages of the economic difficulties of some of the African
countries to exchange money for diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
The real aim of the Taiwan authorities is to split China rather
than to develop economic and trade relations with these African
countries, let alone to offer economic assistance to them.
</P>
<P>
The attempt of the Taiwan authorities will lead to nowhere when
the African countries realized its real purpose, Qian added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
