<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Lashio-Hsenwi road, the
first section of the Lashio-Muse road to link northern Myanmar
with China's Yunnan province, has been put into service, official
daily The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The entire road is scheduled for completion in the middle of
the year at the cost of more than 5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
