<HEADLINE> 264 Centenarians in East Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang province
has 264 centenarians, two of whom are 107 years old, according to
a recent survey by a research center.
</P>
<P>
This is 54.5 percent more than in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The elderly people seem to have five things in common:
</P>
<P>
First, harmonious families and children and grandchildren who
show filial piety; most live with four generations under one roof
and have good family relations.
</P>
<P>
Second, they have good habits, such as getting up early and
going to bed early, getting sufficient sleep and regular exercise.
</P>
<P>
Third, they have a good diet, eating three meals a day at fixed
times of light food; most are vegetarians.
</P>
<P>
Fourth, most are optimistic and broad-minded.
</P>
<P>
Last, a good and unpolluted environment, usually in mountains
or near the seashore, where they breathe fresh air.
</P>
<P>
China has 110 million people at or above the age of 60, and the
number is growing at an annual rate of 3.32 percent. By the end of
the century, China will become a society of aging people, with the
elderly accounting for more than 10 percent of the world's total.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
