<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Announce Legislature Candidates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's National Election
Committee will have completed half of its preparations for the may
29 general election when it releases today its provisional list of
2,303 legislature candidates, local press reported.
</P>
<P>
Home Affairs Minister Moch. Yogie S.M., in his capacity as the
election committee's chairman, will officially released the list
today.
</P>
<P>
The United Development Party's (PPP) list contains 730
candidates, the ruling political grouping Golkar has 829
candidates and the Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) has 744. said
the reports.
</P>
<P>
Public scrutiny of the candidates is scheduled to start on
Tuesday (January 21) and end on February 18, giving the public 28
days to raise complaints or objections against the candidates.
</P>
<P>
According to regulations, the PPP, PDI and Golkar must draft
their final nomination list between February 19 and March 9.
</P>
<P>
The three groupings will contest the may 29 election, vying for
425 of the 500 seats at the House of Representatives. The 75
remaining seats are reserved for members of the armed forces who
do not vote.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 120 million people will attend balloting tents on
election day in the sixth election since 1971 in the country.
</P>
<P>
The ruling Golkar has won each of the five general elections
held since 1971.
</P>
<P>
Golkar is aiming to win 70 percent of the vote in the May 29
poll, two percent higher then its share at the 1992 election.
</P>
</TEXT>
