<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Establishes Water Conservancy Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Traditional water conservancy
in Shanghai has been expanded to function as a network covering
urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
An official at Shanghai water conservancy bureau says that,
with 464 kilometers of seawall, 208 kilometers of flood prevention
wall, and 2,300 kilometers of embankments as a major part of flood
control work, the water conservancy network has played its role in
every flood season.
</P>
<P>
An electronically-controlled Shanghai flood prevention
automatic measuring system was put into use in 1996.
</P>
<P>
In rural areas, the 6,700 electrically run irrigation and
drainage pumping stations, with 275,000 kw of power, have
irrigated almost all cultivated land.
</P>
<P>
An expert in water conservancy pointed out that the water
conservancy network in Shanghai has delivered a means of solving
the problems of flood, drinking water quality and water
environment.
</P>
<P>
Water conservancy functions have multiplied alongside flood
prevention work, and a water conservancy tourism market has
emerged. The aim of Shanghai water conservancy network is to set a
water environment control system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
