<HEADLINE> Canclini Sweeps Women's Titles in Speedskating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Italian Marinella Canclini
recovered from a fall in Friday's 1,500 meters to sweep the
women's 1,000 and 3,000 events Friday at the European short track
speed skating championships in Malmo of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Italian clocked a winning time of one minute
38.535 seconds in the 1,000 meters to edge out Russian Elena
Tikhanina.
</P>
<P>
In the 3,000 meters, Canclini timed 5:36.987 to win the top
place, followed by 16-year-old Dutchwoman Ellen Wiegers.
</P>
<P>
Mirko Vuillermin lead all the way to claim the men's 3,000
title, coming through the last bend in third place.
</P>
<P>
But the 22-year-old Italian made a tactical mistake by
attacking Nicky Gooch too aggressively, the Briton fell and
Vuillermin was disqualified.
</P>
<P>
But another Italian Fabio Carta went on to take the title and
also won the 1,000 meters from Gooch. 
</P>
</TEXT>
