<HEADLINE> Italians Bags Individual Titles in Speedskating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Fabio Carta and Mirko
Vuillermin swept the men's top two standings and Marinella
Canclini took the women's gold medal as Italy clinched both
individual honors Sunday in the European Short Track Speedskating
Championships in Malmo of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Italy also made the winner in the women's relay while the men
finished third during the final session of the three-day inaugural
European Championships which drew 19 nations and regions.
</P>
<P>
Carta won both the 1,000 and 3,000-meter finals for a four-race
total of 13 points while Vuillermin had 12. Bronze medalist Bruno
Loscos of France totaled 7 points.
</P>
<P>
Canclini also took the last two races, the 1,000 and 3,000, to
top the women's final standings with 15 points. Ellen Wiegers of
the Netherlands was runner-up with 11 points and Elena Tichanina
of Russia third with nine points.
</P>
<P>
Britain prevented a clean sweep by the Italians by capturing
the men's relay ahead of the Netherlands and Italy.
</P>
<P>
The World Championships will be held in March at Nagano, Japan,
the site of next year's Winter Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
