<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Growing in Shanghai's Pudong New Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Customs statistics in
Shanghai's Pudong new area indicate that its imports and exports
in 1996 amounted to 8.07 billion US dollars, up 12.25 percent from
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Supported by state management policy, domestic enterprises had
an import and export volume of 4.74 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The processing trade resulted in increased raw material imports
and product exports. Foreign trade companies of state bureaus and
other provinces have set up over 60 branches in Pudong, giving a
push to the area's foreign trade development.
</P>
<P>
The majority of imported goods were mechanical and electrical
products, while exports involved mainly garments.
</P>
<P>
Japan ranked first among trade partners, with 1.95 billion US
dollars in imports and exports, up three percent over 1995. The
United States, Hong Kong, Germany, and France came next. 
</P>
